			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Headquartered in Portland, Oregon&#39;s innovative Eastside Industrial District, <a href="http://www.crowdcompass.com/">CrowdCompass</a> -- the leading Mobile Device Event Platform -- develops and delivers innovative, native mobile Apps for the global conference, event and tradeshow market. CrowdCompass is looking for a full-time copy writer with community management experience to help drive sales. (http://www.crowdcompass.com/)</p>
<p>
	<strong>Responsibilities:</strong><br />
	&bull; Write and edit copy for the website, sales collateral and marketing automation channels<br />
	&bull; Run and manage the team blog, including ghost writing for management when needed<br />
	&bull; Maintain consistency in tone and grammar throughout all writing activities<br />
	&bull; Work with VP of Marketing to ensure copy is on-brand and meets objectives<br />
	&bull; Collaborate with sales and marketing managers as needed</p>
<br />
<p>
	<strong>Requirements:</strong><br />
	&bull; 2+ years of web writing experience and social media community management<br />
	&bull; Meticulous editing skills<br />
	&bull; Understanding of why content strategy matters</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>Bonus:</strong><br />
	&bull; Experience managing a company blog<br />
	&bull; Experience with keyword usage and an understanding of SEO<br />
	&bull; Experience with social media marketing<br />
	&bull; Experience reaching out to new partners for guest blogging spots<br />
	&bull; Experience using listening tools such as Radian6, Sysomos or NetVibes.</p>
<p>
	<br />
	<strong>How to Apply:</strong><br />
	Email a cover letter and resume to klong@crowdcompass.com<br />
	Title your email: &quot;Freelance Copy Writer Resume/Cover&quot;<br />
	Cover letter should include:<br />
	1) Why are you interested in working for CrowdCompass?<br />
	2) Summarize how your experience fits each of the listed qualifications of the position.<br />
	3) Links to 2 writing samples you have created. One was a serious/business tone and one with a fun/social tone.</p>
